Art,

To establish a fact you have to have a witness. Anagrams and ciphers
have no witnesses. There are exceptions like Jonson's FBACON and
FBACONPOET and Pope's cipher in which the statue of Shakespeare points
to a FBACON or maybe its FRANCIS BACON. Pope raised the money and had
the loopy-looking thing installed--the Bard looks quite drunk--so we
can suspect that Pope put the cipher there. It's pretty obvious that
Pope knew. Of course the Westminster plaque was defaced by authorities
as soon as the Baconians found it.

Anagrams are not evidence because they're anonymous. The law and
science, that is proofs, rely on witnesses and expert witness.

