beneath Mt. Etna, but that's about it. In fact, according to many
accounts, when Hephaestus was cast down from Olympus, he was injured,
but was rescued near Lemnos by the Nereids Thetis and Eurynome, who hid
him from his mother Hera in their submarine grotto. There Hephaestus
first began his work as skilled artisan, fashioning jewelry from coral
reefs.

