Hephaestus was hardly a heroic figure; indeed, in most mythological
accounts, he is if anything a comic figure. According to Hesiod, Hera
gave birth to him by parthogenesis, in a fit of pique at her husband,
Zeus, who had given birth to Athena without her involvement. Hephaestus
was cast out of Olympus by Hera, who was disillusioned by his deformity.
He was also famously cuckolded by his wife Aphrodite with Ares, the war
god. Indeed, Homer recounts the construction by Hephaestus of a
concealed net of chains in which Aphrodite and Ares were entrapped
during one of the former's acts of infidelity.

